 CMD  = default command we can override
------

  CMD defines the default command a container  runs when it start 

Example: CMD ["node","server.js"]

When you run the cotainer 
>> docker run myapp
Docker executes 
>> node server.js

But this can be overridden easily :
EX:
>> docker run myapp node test.js 
Now the docker runs 
>> node test.js

ENTRYPOINT 
------------
   ENTRYPOINT defines the main executable that always runs

EX:
ENTRYPOINT ["node"]
CMD ["server.js"]

When the container start this files runs:
>> node server.js

But if user runs: 
>>docker run myapp test.js 

Docker runs 
>> node test.js

Because : 
ENTRYPOINT = node 
CMD = server.js (default argument)

So docker combines them:
ENTRYPOINT + CMD


We can also use the Entrypoint to run the scripts in advance like 
ENTRYPOINT [ "./firstrunthis.sh"] 


